title: Monster A-Go Go
description:
MONSTER A-GO GO (1965)

Directed by Bill Rebane and Sheldon S. Seymour (Herschell Gordon Lewis)

Notoriously terrible film, worse than you ever imagined a film could be.  Herschell Lewis purchased the unfinished "Terror at Halfday" from director Bill Rebane, added some "rock" music and "sexy" scenes, and penned surreal narration to make the thing seem mysterious. Essentially a space capsule returns to earth, lands in a field in Wisconsin, and the astronaut goes missing. Very tall man in a space suit with horrible skin disease is terrorizing the countryside near the capsule. Coincidence? Oh wait it gets better. Featured on Mystery Science Theater 3000 and (later) TCM Underground.
